description:
An All-New Marvel NOW! ongoing series inspired by the television series. Although this title does not have the 'Avengers NOW!' badge, it is a part of the latest wave. This series follows the team of Agent Couslon. It had a spin-off series named Howling Commandos of S.H.I.E.L.D., which blasted from the pages of issue 9 of this series. This series lasted for a total of 12 issues before it was replaced with the Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. ongoing series.

deck: A short comic book story about an old woman with nothing to lose.
description:
Savings Account is a short story (12 pages) created by writer Juliana Azevedo and artist Mauricio Pommella, and self-published under the label "TheSoulSurfer". It is available as print version and digital download, and has been featured in Top Shelf's online comics program, Top Shelf 2.0.

"Inspired by the news about an old woman who robs a bank, we took this as a storytelling exercise inventing a plausible reason for the robbery." -- by Pommella.

description:
Scott Lang is trying to do his best as Ant-Man as he receives his very own ongoing series under the "Avengers NOW!" banner, written by Nick Spencer. The series ran for only 5 issues and was continued in Ant-Man: Last Days due to the Secret Wars crossover. It also had an Ant-Man Annual issue. After Secret Wars, the series returned as "The Astonishing Ant-Man" with a new number 1.

Collected Editions

  • Marvel's Ant-Man Prelude (#1)
  • Ant-Man: Second-Chance Man (#1-5)

Translated into Spanish.
name: Ant-Man
